mv - mv stands for Move. This command is used to move a file or directory. It is also used to rename a file or directory.

Following are the commands related to mv which are as follows :-

1) To rename a file :
   Syntax - mv <renaming_filename> <new_filename>
   
2) To rename a directory :
   Syntax - mv <renaming_directory_name> <new_directory_name>
   
3) To move multiple files to a specific directory :
   Syntax - mv *
   
4) To move only those files that doesnot exists :
   Syntax - mv -u
